> [randomshits](#comment_366_1CuFETj5LtyEduzaoAcdv9sMAQtYRqjqDY): About four years ago I started to vape as an alternative to smoking cigarettes for 20 years. I did that for about two years until my lymph node on my neck got swollen and wouldn't go down. I went to an ENT for an examination and he couldn't give me an prognosis of what caused it without a biopsy because much like other exposures to chemicals; vaping, the metals used for the coil, the additive, and chemicals used for the dyes and flavoring were not yet regulated nor given any long term studies. [...]

I can understand this but there is a few guidelines I would recommend:

1. Stick to high quality flavors, VG and PG. European or US made only. 
2. Avoid Nicotine. It does not play well in vapes. A cigarette is honestly healthier than vaping nicotine. Every negative study about vaping is usually a cheap juice or a nicotine containing juice.
3. Avoid butter/cookie/nut flavours. They're just bad for you. These synthesized flavors were never meant to be heated and inhaled.
4. Stick to plain fruit flavours. Good quality only. If a flavour gives you issues. Isolate it and avoid it.
5. Use Smok Beast tanks with prepacked coils. This might seem a downgrade, but if you count up the amount of time you spend building coils and packing cotton and then prepping it without spilling, it is way easier and cheaper to just use the prepacked Smok Beast coils. Never had any issues with them. Many issues with RBA however. Have tried over 5 different tanks and various high quality coils and cotton. I just don't like it. 
6. Use a lower wattage - 60W max. Just enough to atomize and get the flavour to come through. You don't need to rip clouds like a steamtrain. Your batteries (between charges) and coils will last longer too. 
7. If you're still having problems, try reducing the PG to a low amount. 

This is what worked for me.

I guess things are different now, but also the guy I buy my alien coils from uses American made NI80 and I only buy Aussie or American juice that's known reputable.

Cannot stress this enough. Quality coils/cotton/juice is crucial to avoid vape health issues.
